<div class="title">
==Description==
</div>

{{Blurimage|file=Traveler.png|caption=An Image of Level 413 Hydroflow Sunset.}}
'''Level 413''' is known as <ruby>Hydroflow Sunset<rp>(</rp><rt>sunset celebrating your death</rt><rp>)</rp></ruby> among explorers. An obvious feature that can be seen at this level is the bright sun on the sky and the pool-like structure around the level. It is a pool room under sunset in nature, with pools containing a crude-oil-like structure with no odor or flavor. People entering this level described it as sticky and slippery. It was discovered to contain unknown sub-levels under its pool structure. Its maze-like structure also makes it extremely difficult to explore and learn about the full appearance of the level. It also has the name "Sticky Heaven", as its temperature could automatically adjust to be the optimum temperature for humans. Natural wind is present at the level, which gives the feeling of standing on the beach. Almond water and food supply are adequate in some areas, such as square-shaped grids on the white-tiled wall. 

The architectural style at this level can be described as "rectangular." Few curved areas are found at this level. Most areas at this level are straight with sharp right-angled corners. This has been proven to be related to the properties of variations of bismuth compounds (mainly tetrabismuth tricarbride Bi4C3), which inherited the properties of bismuth to naturally form rectangular structures. No conflict structures are found, and all the C-E districts are linked together by paths or hallways. Curved areas are hypothesized to be generated by some <ruby>curved bondings<rp>(</rp><rt>C≈C bonds</rt><rp>)</rp></ruby> or irreversible changes. Scientists are actively restarting the exploration of the level to investigate the nature of curved areas. 

Unlike <ruby>pool rooms<rp>(</rp><rt>slippery maze</rt><rp>)</rp></ruby> in [[Level 37]], the pools in this level contain a liquid that reflects only dark light. Therefore, some explorers who have visited this level have mentioned that they are unable to see the bottom of the water. According to recent discoveries, the liquid in the pool has unknown physical and chemical properties. It is found to be around 30°C and has a pH of around 0.24 in darker areas, such as areas covered by walls and the rooftop. However, its temperature is measured to be 1649°C and a nearly neutral pH is recorded in areas shone by the sunlight,for example, the large area covered by liquid, known as "the sea." Some people guessed that the liquid absorbs energy at an extremely high rate. Others thought that energy was continuously supplied under the deep, dark pool, like a heater. Up until now, there have been no recorded explorers who have reached the bottom of the pool. Besides being energy-absorbing, the liquid also has a unique texture. It is found to be thick, or even hard, like rocks in some areas. Explorers discovered that the white tiles on the walls could be a reason for affecting the liquid's thickness. The liquid is continuously flowing in the room, despite its thickness or hardness. It has been found that the liquid is flowing in the same direction in some areas. This could happen when <ruby>entities<rp>(</rp><rt>you, in another form</rt><rp>)</rp></ruby> absorb carbo-liquid for growth or body metabolism. 
{{Blurimage|file=屏幕截图 2024-04-21 133214.png|caption=An image showing the "sea" of level 413,containing the crude-oil-like liquid}}

Random doodles are found in some dark corners of the level. The doodles are said to have been drawn by previous <ruby>explorers<rp>(</rp><rt>you, in other form(s)</rt><rp>)</rp></ruby> who visited this level. However, none of the explorers who have successfully left the level remember drawing the doodles. The doodles are mainly <ruby>spider-like human models<rp>(</rp><rt>Astrix 04 blood shame</rt><rp>)</rp></ruby>, <ruby>long-handed organisms<rp>(</rp><rt>variation of error</rt><rp>)</rp></ruby>, and <ruby>special linkages among some round structures<rp>(</rp><rt>energy chains</rt><rp>)</rp></ruby>. No records of the discoveries of doodles are present. 
{{Blurimage|file=R-D26.png|caption=An isolated room in district D-26.}}
Completely isolated rooms with no entrances are found in the D-26 district. These rooms are not available for entry unless the white-tiled wall has been crashed. Due to the special structure of the carbon tile, it is very difficult to break. Pillars are usually found in these rooms.

==== The Pool in Nature====
Pools at this level are found to contain unknown substances. It is detected to contain carbon with a molecular weight of 1388274.84095. It also has bonding similar to starch, which makes it harden when pressure is exerted on it. Anything with weight can stay on the liquid surface, but staying for a long time will result in sinking. The strong bonding of the liquid molecules makes its hardness similar to that of diamond, which is almost impossible to break. However, the liquid is still able to flow around. The reason behind this is currently unknown. Due to its special properties, the substance is given the name <ruby>"carbo-liquid-1388274"<rp>(</rp><rt>the fluid of beauty and pure</rt><rp>)</rp></ruby>.

{{Blurimage|file=pond413.png|caption=A pond in Level 413}}
The distribution of the pools is similar to natural landscape. Pool "rivers" are found in the form of curved hallways. The hallways in this level are all curved, except the one leading to the exit. Ponds also exists in an extremely small amount in the level. The ponds are usually, but not always, round in color, similar to those huge fuel tanks. The carbo-liquid in ponds are found to have a little pungent and irritating odor, it is not sure what the composition of the liquid is.  

===Variations and Behaviors===
Level 413 is extremely stable in nature. That is why it does not contain too many unexpected areas or <ruby>errors<rp>(</rp><rt>technical failures</rt><rp>)</rp></ruby>. One of the rarely-discovered regions is the Cyan-Blue region. It is a region with a cyan sky during the day. It is discovered by <ruby>destroying<rp>(</rp><rt style="color:red;">deleting</rt><rp>)</rp></ruby> a proportion of a room in the level, resulting in a time error. High round pillars are also found in this level, oddly. It is not sure whether the pillars are also an unexpected behavior exhibited at this level. Staircases are also found near pools and retangular structures. Currently, no information can be obtained about what is the purpose of these staircases, or what they are designed for. Some scientists of this level suspected that some kind of entity is using these staircases for rapid movement between their essential areas or habitats.  

=== Level of <ruby>Giant<rp>(</rp><rt>The Hexamax</rt><rp>)</rp></ruby>===
Everything at this level is huge. For instance, the pools are found to be on average 1324m x 1549m. Pillars [see variations and behaviors] are almost a swimming pool size on its cross-section face and have a height of 2000m or higher. The rooftops of the hallways are also measured to be around 38 meters. It is so huge that the wall looks like a white, flat surface, despite its grids. Staircases with around 25m a step are sometimes found in this level. Owing to the behemothic sizes of the objects, scientists believed that huge entities are present in this level.  

